==Scottish Gaelic==

===Etymology===
Old Irish [[fér]], Welsh [[gwair]]

===Noun===
'''feur''' {{m}}
#[[grass]], [[pasture]], [[herbage]], [[hay]]

===Verb===
'''feur'''
#[[graze]], feed on grass
#feed cattle in choice pasture
#* Dh' fheur e an t-each.
#** He grazed the horse.

